# CHANGELOG - ORIC-1 Emulator

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [1.0.0-beta.5] - 2026-02-23

### Fixed - HIRES Rendering & Keyboard Automation (Sprint 16b)
- **HIRES mode detection**: fixed bit check in $26A (bit 1, not bit 2)
  ROM HIRES routine writes $03 to $26A; was checking wrong bit
- **HIRES attribute detection**: use `(byte & 0x60) == 0` instead of `!(byte & 0x40)`
  Bytes 0x20-0x3F are pixel data, not serial attributes (matches Oricutron ULA)
- **HIRES bit 7 inversion**: when bit 7 set, ink/paper colors XOR with 7
  Enables proper rendering of inverted pixel blocks
- **HIRES charset address**: use $9800 in HIRES mode (not $B400, which is
  overwritten by HIRES bitmap at $A000-$BF3F)

### Added
- `oric_keyboard_press_char()`: press a key by ASCII character (for automation)
- `oric_keyboard_release_all()`: release all keys (clear matrix to 0xFF)
- `--type-keys CYCLES:TEXT` CLI option: simulate keyboard input at given cycle
  Supports `\n` for Return, `\pN` for N-second pause
- Poker game (poker-asn.tap) now renders correctly in HIRES mode

### Changed
- Refactored keyboard.c: shared `char_map[128]` between SDL and non-SDL builds
- Version updated to 1.0.0-beta.5

## [1.0.0-beta.4] - 2026-02-22

### Added - CLOAD via ROM Patching (Sprint 16a)
- CLOAD command support: tape programs load when user types CLOAD in BASIC
- ROM patching intercepts getsync ($E696) and readbyte ($E630) routines
- TAP file buffered in memory for sequential reading by ROM routines
- Sync byte detection (0x16) and byte-by-byte tape reading
- CPU register injection (A register, Z flag, $002F store)
- `-t file.tap` without `-f`: tape available for CLOAD (ROM patching mode)
- `-t file.tap -f`: fast load with direct memory injection (no CLOAD needed)

### Changed
- `emulator_t` struct: added tapebuf, tapelen, tapeoffs, tape_loaded fields
- `tape_patches()` called after each CPU instruction in emulation loop
- Tape loading split: buffered mode (default) vs fast-load injection (`-f`)
- Help text updated to clarify `-f` fast-load behavior
- `emulator_cleanup()` frees tape buffer
- Version updated to 1.0.0-beta.4

## [1.0.0-beta.3] - 2026-02-22

### Fixed - PSG Bus Protocol & Keyboard (Sprint 15b)
- Fixed PSG bus decode: CA2=BC1, CB2=BDIR (was incorrectly swapped)
- Fixed ghost keypresses (stars on screen): VIA PB3 keyboard scan feedback
- PSG Port A input callback returns keyboard matrix state (active low)
- PSG registers 14-15 (I/O ports) initialized to 0xFF (no keys pressed)
- AY_NUM_REGISTERS expanded from 14 to 16 to include I/O ports

### Fixed - HIRES Video Rendering
- Fixed HIRES bottom 3 text rows: serial attribute processing (ink/paper/inverse) was missing, rendered white-on-black only
- Added character bit 7 inversion support in HIRES text rows
- Added auto-detection of HIRES mode from RAM $26A bit 2 (HTEFLAG)

### Added - SDL2 Keyboard Mapping
- ORIC keyboard matrix header `include/io/keyboard.h`
- SDL2 keycode → ORIC matrix mapping (64 keys, QWERTY layout from Oricutron)
- Symbolic keyboard mapping via SDL_TEXTINPUT (`--keyboard azerty` or `-k azerty`)
- Character → ORIC key combo table derived from ROM tables at $FF70/$FFB0
- Works with any PC keyboard layout (AZERTY, QWERTZ, etc.)
- `oric_keyboard_t` struct with init/reset/event handling and layout selection
- `oric_keyboard_set_layout()` function for runtime layout switching
- Pressed key tracking with automatic ORIC Shift management
- SDL2 event polling in main loop: keyboard input, F5=reset, F10=quit, F11=fullscreen, F12=screenshot
- VIA Port B read callback for PB3 keyboard scan result
- PSG Port A input callback for keyboard row data

### Changed
- `emulator_t` now uses `oric_keyboard_t` struct instead of raw array
- PSG bus decode triggered on PCR, ORA, and ORB writes (was ORB only)
- Version updated to 1.0.0-beta.3
- `keyboard.c` rewritten with SDL2 mapping table and oric_keyboard_t API

## [1.0.0-beta.2] - 2026-02-22

### Added - Video Integration & Debug Export (Sprint 15)
- Video system (`video_t`) integrated into emulator main loop
- Charset ROM connected to video renderer from memory subsystem
- Video frame rendering after each CPU frame (20000 cycles)
- New export module `src/video/export.c` with `include/video/export.h`
- PPM export (P6 binary format): zero-dependency RGB888 screenshot
- BMP export (24-bit uncompressed): BITMAPFILEHEADER + BITMAPINFOHEADER + bottom-up pixels
- ASCII export (ANSI true-color): terminal display with `\x1b[48;2;R;G;Bm` escape codes
- Auto-detect export format from file extension (.ppm/.bmp)
- CLI option `--screenshot FILE`: take screenshot at exit
- CLI option `--screenshot-at CYCLES:FILE`: screenshot after N cycles
- CLI option `--frame-dump DIR`: export frames to directory
- CLI option `--frame-dump-interval N`: dump every Nth frame (default: 50)
- 11 new video tests in `tests/unit/test_video.c`
- Tests cover: PPM/BMP/ASCII export, text/HIRES rendering, null params, ROM boot screenshot
- `make test-video` target added to build system

### Changed
- `emulator_t` struct now includes `video_t video` member
- `emulator_init()` initializes video and connects charset ROM
- `emulator_run()` renders video frame and calls renderer after each CPU frame
- `emulator_cleanup()` cleans up video and renderer
- Version updated to 1.0.0-beta.2
- Test suite expanded from 148 to 159 tests (148 + 11 video export)
- Total test count: 159 tests, 100% pass rate

## [1.0.0-beta] - 2026-02-22

### Added - ROM Compatibility Tests (Sprint 14)
- New test file `tests/unit/test_rom.c` with 12 tests validating real ORIC-1 ROM
- ROM loading validation (16384 bytes, basic10.rom)
- Reset vector verification ($FFFC-$FFFD = $F42D)
- IRQ vector verification ($FFFE-$FFFF = $0228)
- NMI vector verification ($FFFA-$FFFB = $022B)
- CPU boot to correct PC after reset
- ROM boot stability test (100K cycles without crash)
- VIA initialization verification during boot (ROM writes to VIA after RAM test)
- Screen RAM ($BB80-$BFDF) write verification during boot
- Zero-page system variable initialization check
- ROM checksum validation
- Performance benchmark: 1M cycles in ~10ms (~90+ MHz equivalent, target <100ms)

### Added - Build System Targets
- `make test-rom` - Run ROM compatibility tests
- `make valgrind` - Run all tests under Valgrind for memory leak detection
- `make static-analysis` - Run static analysis with extra warning flags

### Fixed
- Memory map comment in `include/memory/memory.h`: VIA correctly at $0300-$030F (was incorrectly documented as $B400-$B4FF)
- `strncpy` truncation warnings in `src/hostfs/hostfs.c` replaced with `snprintf`

### Changed
- Test suite expanded from 136 to 148 tests (136 unit + 12 ROM compatibility)
- Total test count: 148 tests, 100% pass rate

## [1.0.0-alpha] - 2026-02-22

### Added - CPU 6502 (Sprint 1-2)
- Complete MOS 6502 CPU emulation with all 151 official opcodes
- All 13 addressing modes: Implicit, Accumulator, Immediate, Zero Page, Zero Page X/Y,
  Absolute, Absolute X/Y, Indirect, Indexed Indirect, Indirect Indexed, Relative
- Cycle-accurate instruction timing with page-crossing penalty
- BCD arithmetic (ADC/SBC decimal mode) following NMOS 6502 behavior
- 6502 JMP indirect page boundary bug emulation
- NMI and IRQ interrupt handling with proper priority (NMI > IRQ)
- Full disassembler with operand formatting
- CPU state string output for debugging

### Added - Memory System (Sprint 3)
- 64KB addressable memory space ($0000-$FFFF)
- RAM: $0000-$BFFF (48KB)
- ROM: $C000-$FFFF (16KB) with ROM/RAM overlay banking
- I/O space at $0300-$03FF with callback routing
- Memory-mapped VIA 6522 at $0300-$030F
- Memory access tracing for debugging
- ROM loading from file, charset ROM loading
- Interrupt vectors always read from ROM

### Added - I/O System (Sprint 3-4)
- Complete MOS 6522 VIA emulation (all 16 registers)
- Timer 1: One-shot and free-running modes with latch reload
- Timer 2: One-shot mode with counting
- Interrupt generation (IFR/IER) with proper set/clear logic
- Port A/B with data direction registers and callbacks
- Shift register support
- Keyboard matrix (8x8) with column select scanning
- Cassette motor control and bit read interface
- CA1/CA2/CB1/CB2 interrupt triggers

### Added - Video System (Sprint 5-6)
- ORIC text mode: 40x28 characters from charset ROM
- ORIC HIRES mode: 240x200 pixel rendering
- Serial color attributes (ink 0-7, paper 16-23)
- Inverse video attribute support (codes 28/29)
- Character rendering from 8-byte charset patterns
- Framebuffer-based rendering (240x224 RGB)
- SDL2 renderer with window creation (conditional compilation)
- Headless mode fallback (no SDL2 dependency)
- Text helper functions: clear, putchar, getchar, scroll
- HIRES helper functions: clear, set_pixel, get_pixel

### Added - Audio System (Sprint 7)
- Complete AY-3-8910 PSG emulation
- 3 independent tone generators with 12-bit period
- Noise generator with 5-bit period and 17-bit LFSR
- Mixer control (tone/noise enable per channel)
- Per-channel volume with 4-bit level or envelope mode
- 16 envelope shapes (attack, alternate, hold combinations)
- Sample generation with clock-accurate counters
- SDL2 audio output with callback (conditional compilation)
- Headless audio mode

### Added - Storage System (Sprint 8-9)
- Complete .TAP cassette format support
  - Read/write headers (sync, marker, type, addresses, name)
  - Data block read/write with checksum
  - Fast load support (entire file in memory)
  - BASIC-to-TAP conversion (tap_from_basic)
  - Binary-to-TAP conversion (tap_from_binary)
- Sedoric disk filesystem
  - Disk image create/load/save
  - 42 tracks x 17 sectors x 256 bytes
  - Sector-level read/write
  - System sector initialization with SED signature
- FDC WD1793 disk controller
  - Type I commands: Restore, Seek, Step (in/out)
  - Type II commands: Read Sector, Write Sector
  - DRQ/IRQ generation
  - Force Interrupt command
  - 256-byte sector buffer with sequential access

### Added - Host Filesystem (Sprint 10-11)
- Host directory mounting with path validation
- Read-only mount option
- File operations: open, close, read, write, seek
- File handle management (up to 8 simultaneous)
- ORIC-to-host path translation
- Host-to-ORIC name conversion (uppercase)
- Directory listing
- File delete and rename operations
- VFS abstraction layer: TAPE, DISK, HOSTFS mount types

### Added - Conversion Tools
- `bas2tap`: Convert BASIC text files to .TAP format
- `bin2tap`: Convert binary files to .TAP with load/exec address
- `tap2sedoric`: TAP to Sedoric disk converter (framework)

### Added - Configuration & Utilities
- INI file configuration parser (key=value, comments, sections)
- Configuration get/set with string, int, and bool types
- Configuration save to file
- Logging system with DEBUG/INFO/WARNING/ERROR levels
- Timestamped log output

### Added - Main Emulator
- Full emulation loop: CPU + VIA timer sync per frame
- I/O callback wiring (CPU <-> Memory <-> VIA)
- VIA IRQ -> CPU IRQ callback chain
- Headless mode with cycle limit for testing
- Signal handling (SIGINT/SIGTERM for clean shutdown)
- TAP file loading with memory injection
- Command line options: tape, disk, rom, hostfs, fast-load, headless, cycles, verbose

### Added - Build System
- Updated Makefile with all source files
- Individual test targets: test-cpu, test-memory, test-io, test-storage, test-system
- SDL2 conditional compilation (SDL2=1)
- Debug/Release build modes (DEBUG=1)

### Added - Test Suite (136 tests, 100% pass)
- CPU tests: 74 tests covering all opcodes, addressing modes, flags, interrupts
- Memory tests: 19 tests covering RAM, ROM banking, I/O routing, tracing
- VIA I/O tests: 24 tests covering registers, timers, interrupts, ports
- Storage tests: 12 tests covering Sedoric disk and FDC WD1793
- System integration tests: 7 tests including Fibonacci, multiply, CPU+VIA wiring

